Notes: No explicit path for row_id in the ontology; it is an internal CSV row identifier and maps best to the main entity as a local identifier or index without further semantic mapping.

patient_id represents a unique patient identifier; path 23 goes from ProblemCondition to Patient and then to PatientIdentifier, which semantically fits best as it captures patient identity rather than the patient entity itself or other patient attributes.

diagnosis_code maps directly to the ProblemCondition's hasCode property to Code entity (path 5). Although there is a 2-hop path to Code's properties (paths 66-68), the direct hasCode link is optimal for representing the diagnosis code itself.

created_at is a timestamp for the ProblemCondition instance creation; path 14 directly links ProblemCondition to dateTime which is appropriate. Alternative datetime paths (e.g., hasOnsetDateTime, hasRecordDateTime) are semantically different and less fitting for creation timestamp.

org_code identifies the organization providing data; path 8 leads to DataProviderInstitute, and path 79 extends to its Code, capturing the code of the organization, which fits org_code better than just linking to the institute (path 8) alone.

org_name corresponds to the name of the data provider institute; path 81 is a 2-hop path from ProblemCondition to DataProviderInstitute and then to its name property, semantically precise for organization names.
